# Scroll Progress Bar

## What It Is
A thin horizontal line fixed at the very top of the viewport.
Fills left to right as the user scrolls down the page.
Sits above the navbar (highest z-index on the page).

## Behavior
- Starts empty (width 0%) at top of page
- Fills to 100% at bottom of page
- Smooth fill — no jumps
- Does not affect page layout (fixed position)

## Implementation
- "use client" component
- Use framer-motion useScroll and useSpring
- useScroll gives scrollYProgress (0 to 1)
- useSpring smooths the value: stiffness 100, damping 30, restDelta 0.001
- motion.div with scaleX driven by spring value
- transformOrigin: left

## Style
- Fixed position: top 0, left 0
- Full width (w-full)
- Height: 3px
- Background: var(--text-primary)
- z-index: 9999
- origin-left for scale transform

## Rules
- "use client" directive required
- No other dependencies beyond framer-motion
- Added to layout.tsx inside ThemeProvider above {children}
